name: XTP/dITP diphosphatase
reaction: (1) XTP + H2O = XMP + diphosphate [RN:R02720]; (2) dITP + H2O = dIMP + diphosphate [RN:R03531]; (2) ITP + H2O = IMP + diphosphate [RN:R00720]
comment: The enzymes from the bacterium Escherichia coli and the archaea Methanococcus jannaschii and Archaeoglobus fulgidus are highly specific for XTP, dITP and ITP. The activity is dependent on divalent cations, Mg2+ is preferred.
